Endpoints.Name: Retrieve all transactions for a user
Endpoints.Description: Requires **transactions:read:all** scope. Transactions usually start around the account opening date however in most cases we only retrive the last 12 months before the connection was created. The Opening Date is available at the /accounts endpoint.
Endpoints.Summary: Retrieve all transactions for a user

400.Name: response400
400.Description: Unsuccessful Response - Bad request - Missing query parameters - Missing body properties

401.Name: response401
401.Description: Unsuccessful Response - Not authorised - Missing authorization header - Invalid access Token

Parameters.Name: ids
Parameters.Description: Filter on the transaction's Ids (maximum allowed 50)

Parameters.Name: limit
Parameters.Description: The total number of records to retrieve

Parameters.Name: offset
Parameters.Description: The offset at which to start retrieving records

Parameters.Name: startDate
Parameters.Description: The earliest date to receive transactions from (inclusive)

Parameters.Name: endDate
Parameters.Description: The latest date to receive transactions from (inclusive)

Parameters.Name: startDateModified
Parameters.Description: The earliest date the transactions were modified (inclusive)

Parameters.Name: endDateModified
Parameters.Description: The latest date the transactions were modified (inclusive)

Parameters.Name: text
Parameters.Description: The text to filter transactions descriptions/notes by

Parameters.Name: categoryId
Parameters.Description: The category id to filter transactions by

Parameters.Name: accountId
Parameters.Description: The account id to filter transactions by

Parameters.Name: accountIds
Parameters.Description: The account ids to filter transactions by

Parameters.Name: projectId
Parameters.Description: The project id to filter transactions by

Parameters.Name: projectIds
Parameters.Description: The project ids to filter transactions by

Parameters.Name: creditDebitIndicator
Parameters.Description: Filter transactions depending on whether they are credit or debit transactions

Parameters.Name: hasProject
Parameters.Description: Filter on whether transaction has an attached project

Parameters.Name: onlyCount
Parameters.Description: Ensures ONLY the count of transactions is returned in the meta object

Parameters.Name: contains
Parameters.Description: Filter on the beginning of words of a transaction's clean description or beginning of transaction amount

Parameters.Name: hasEnhancedCategory
Parameters.Description: A property to check exists within a transaction

Parameters.Name: counterpartyIds
Parameters.Description: Filter on the transaction's counterparty Id

Parameters.Name: enhancedCategories
Parameters.Description: An enhanced category to filter transactions by in the form of ${categoryField}:${categoryValue}

Errors.ErrorMessage: Unsuccessful Response - Bad request - Missing query parameters - Missing body properties
Unsuccessful Response - Not authorised - Missing authorization header - Invalid access Token

Endpoints.Name: Retrieve spending analysis by categories, projects and accounts
Endpoints.Description:
Defaults to all categories and accounts if none specified.
The categories field in the response has a breakdown of the total by categories for the given periods. You can expect to also receive the breakdown for income and transfer categories.
The 'total' field in the response calculates the total outgoing expenditure for the given periods. This calculation do not include income and transfers.
Categories under the transfer group are the only ones that can appear twice showing income and expenditure separately
Requires **spending_analysis:read** scope.
Endpoints.Summary: Retrieve spending analysis by categories, projects and accounts
